==English==

===Etymology===
{{OF.}} ''[[desgouster]]'', "to put off one's appetite", from ''[[des-]]'', "dis-", + ''[[gouster]]'', ''[[goster]]'', "to taste". "Gustat" is taste in Latin also, making it a derivative.

